# STLoop Testing Rules

## Mandatory Test Coverage
When modifying any of these core modules, you MUST add or update corresponding tests:
- `builder.py` -> `tests/unit/test_builder.py` or `tests/integration/test_build_flow.py`
- `flasher.py` -> `tests/unit/test_flasher.py`
- `tester.py` -> `tests/unit/test_tester.py`
- `client.py` -> `tests/unit/test_client.py` or `tests/integration/test_build_flow.py`
- `code_validator.py` -> `tests/unit/test_code_validator.py`

## TDD Workflow
For new features:
1. Write a failing test first
2. Implement minimal code to pass
3. Refactor if needed
4. Verify all related tests pass

## Pytest Markers
- Unit tests: no special marker needed
- Integration tests (need toolchain): `@pytest.mark.integration`
- Hardware tests (need probe): `@pytest.mark.hardware`
- Run unit only: `pytest -m "not integration and not hardware"`

## Mock Guidelines
- Mock LLM responses with fixed code strings, never call real API in tests
- Mock file system operations with `tmp_path` fixture
- Mock pyOCD/hardware with dependency injection or `unittest.mock`
